                <h2>About Dehradun</h2>
                <p>Dehradun, the capital of Uttarakhand, is a picturesque city nestled in the Doon Valley at the foothills of the Himalayas. It boasts a rich cultural heritage blending Garhwali and Kumaoni traditions, renowned educational institutions like The Doon School and Forest Research Institute, and popular tourist destinations such as Robber's Cave and nearby hill stations like Mussoorie. The city's economy thrives on agriculture, tourism, and education, making it a significant hub in northern India.</p>
            </div> 
            <div class="about_dehra">
                <h2>Things to Do in Dehradun</h2>
                <p>Visit <b>Robber's Cave (Guchhupani), Tapkeshwar Temple, Sahastradhara, Mindrolling Monastery, Paltan Bazaar, Dehradun Zoo, Clock Tower Dehradun, Shikhar Falls, Rajaji National Park, Kedarkantha Trek, Tiger View Jungle Camp, Rupin Pass Trek, Kalsi, Rafting in Tiuni</b> and many more you can explore.</p>
                <p>If you are one of those people who enjoy exploring places with a mountainous backdrop, Dehradun is the ideal place for you to visit.It is bordered by the Shivalik range to the south and the Lesser Himalayas to the north, with the Ganges river flowing to its east and the Yamuna river to its west.</p>
                <p>The city enjoys a temperate climate with mild summers and cool winters, making it a popular destination throughout the year. Dehradun is approximately 230 kilometers north of New Delhi and is well-connected by road, rail (Dehradun Railway Station), and air (Jolly Grant Airport). Its strategic location makes it a gateway to nearby hill stations like Mussoorie and pilgrimage sites such as Haridwar and Rishikesh. The city's setting amidst scenic landscapes and proximity to natural attractions enhances its appeal as a cultural, educational, and tourism hub in northern India.</p>
            </div>
